            That I was born with a sun such as thou <br>
            In truth, the luckiest of all was me <br>
            Although all have life, all have energy <br>
            You give me so much more, I will avow <br>

            You shine so bright all day, I wonder how <br>
            The endless warmth of yours envelops me <br>
            You’re always warm for me, Impossibly <br>
            But when dusk comes, with all my heart, I vow <br>

            That I will shine my very best for you <br>
            That on your heart, I’ll place all warmth upon <br>
            That I will shine to keep the dark from you <br>
            Like how, for me, you kept the brightness on <br>
            And when the pitch black night is true <br>
            I’ll take it in pride that I was your son \<br>
